rules: Rule1: Provided that drug Alpha has a patent in region Zeta, then drug Alpha is licensed to company Beta.

Rule3: Drug Alpha is safe, or drug Alpha has a successful efficacy trial.

Rule8: Whenever drug Alpha is licensed to company Beta, then drug Alpha is produced by company Beta.
Rule9: If drug Alpha is licensed to company Beta, then drug Alpha is marketed by company Beta.

Rule18: If it is not the case that if drug Alpha is safe then drug Alpha is effective against disease Gamma, then drug Alpha is recalled.
Rule19: If it is not the case that provided drug Alpha is safe then drug Alpha is effective against disease Gamma, then drug Alpha’s trial is suspended.
Rule20: Provided that drug Alpha is not a generic drug, then drug Alpha is available on the market.
